Finding the remaining capacity to accomodate more rocks and then greedily filling those bags first which require least rocks.
# Approach
1. Create an additional array which stores remaining capacity the 
bags
2. Sort the diff array
3. Allot rocks to these bags greedily which requires least rocks first
4. keep a variable ans, which keeps count of fully filled bags, once additionalRocks goes below 0 or less than min required, break;

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
Nlog(N)
- Space complexity:
O(N)
# Code
