# Intuition
###### First we need to calculate how much `Space` for the `Additional stones`left in each bag.
###### Then we arrange the bags accordingly( `increasing left capcity`)  
###### check the bags are `already full or not` if not full then `keep filling them one by one with additional stones untill no more additional stone left` 

# Approach
1. make a left vector where `left[i]=capacity[i]-rocks[i]`
2. sort the left vector in ascending order
3. traverse the vector 
4. if the element is already 0(bag is already full) append the answer count
5. else append the answer count and subtract the element from additional rock (filling the bag)
6. if additional rock becomes 0 (no additional rock are left) then stop
7. return the answer count  

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: )(n)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

