# Approach
```
First We will create a 2D array where difference between 
the capacity and currently filled capacity of rocks, 
current strength of rocks, total capacity of rocks 
are stored respectively.
Then we will sort based on the differences. 
here we will think **greedily** because we are sure that 
if we want maximum then we should start filling the bags 
which need minimum additional rocks.
After Sorting we will just iterate through the array
and will try decreasing the additional rocks until it becomes
zero or is less than some difference which we cannot fulfill by 
adding the extra rocks to that bag.
Then simply we will iterate through array and see the postions 
where we have the bags filled with full capacity.

```

