# Approach

Initially, I found the number of the empty places for each bags. ```AdditionalPlaces``` array represants these places. The first for loop does this.

Then I sorted ```AdditionalPlaces``` by ascending order.

The belowing for fills bags as follows: in which bags have more empty places than others then it fills earlier. 
```
for(int i=0;i<length;i++){
