# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
The initial rocks filled in each bag being given, our only task is to find the no. of bags that are filled to their capacity and the bags with minimum difference between their initial value and their capacity.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
So, we take an array called $$diff$$ to store the difference for each $$ith $$ bag and then sort it.
After sorting, we will end up with the array starting with bags that are already filled to their capacity followed by the bags that require least number of rocks in ascending order.
So, we run a loop for all the bags until 
1. all the bags are filled, or 
2. all additional rocks are used.

Initialise, $$ans$$ = 0

In each iteration of the loop, we have two conditions:
1. $$diff[i]$$ = 0
2. $$diff[i]$$ != 0

For the first condition, we increment our $$ans$$ by 1 and jump to next iteration.
For the second condition, we check if we have enough addtional rocks to fill the difference in each bag, i.e., $$extra - diff[i] >= 0$$, if yes, we have found another bag that can be filled completely, so we increment $$ans$$ by 1. Next, we update the additional rocks left by updating it as $$additional rocks = additional rocks - diff[i]$$

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n)$$ + $$O(n.log(n))$$(for sorting)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:$$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

Please upvote if you liked my approach and comment down if you have a better approach.
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maximumBags(int[] capacity, int[] rocks, int extra) {
        int ans = 0;
        int n = capacity.length;
        int[] diff = new int[n];
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            diff[i] = capacity[i] - rocks[i];
        }
        Arrays.sort(diff);
        int i = 0;
        while (i < n && extra > 0) {
            if (diff[i] == 0) ++ans;
            else {
                if (extra - diff[i] >= 0) ++ans;
                extra -= diff[i];
            }
            ++i;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

