# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Sort the differences in ascending order. Fill the bags with remaining additional rocks until all are used.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Sorting and summing.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: We are iterating the loop that takes O(n) time. But the arrays.sort() operation takes $$O(nlogn)$$ time. So, in total it will be: $$O(nlogn)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ --> 

- Space complexity: As we have declared another array int[] diffs of size n, the space complexity will be: $$O(n)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int maximumBags(int[] capacity, int[] rocks, int additionalRocks) {
        int n = rocks.length;
        int[] diffs = new int[n];
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            diffs[i] = capacity[i]-rocks[i];
        }
        Arrays.sort(diffs);

        int bagsFilled = 0;
        int rocksTaken = 0;

        for(int diff: diffs){
            rocksTaken+= diff;
            if(rocksTaken>additionalRocks){
                break;
            }
            bagsFilled++;
        }
        return bagsFilled;
    }
}
```

